        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Juno is a Go implementation of a StarkNet full node client made with ‚ù§Ô∏è by Nethermind.</p><p>We are working hard for our first release, until that happen, what you can do?</p><p>Let's discover <strong>Juno in less than 5 min</strong>.</p><h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="what-youll-need">What you'll need<a class="hash-link" href="#what-youll-need" title="Direct link to heading">‚Äã</a></h2><ul><li><a href="https://go.dev/doc/install" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Golang</a> version 1.18 for build and run the project.</li><li><a href="https://www.cairo-lang.org/docs/quickstart.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cairo-lang</a> if you want to do <code>starknet_call</code> command.</li></ul><h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="installing">Installing<a class="hash-link" href="#installing" title="Direct link to heading">‚Äã</a></h3><p>You can get all the dependencies running the next command:</p><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">$ go get -u github.com/NethermindEth/juno </span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div><h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="running-the-node">Running the node<a class="hash-link" href="#running-the-node" title="Direct link to heading">‚Äã</a></h2><h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="compiling-directly">Compiling directly<a class="hash-link" href="#compiling-directly" title="Direct link to heading">‚Äã</a></h3><p>If you want to run the node, you can compile directly the app using:</p><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">$ </span><span class="token function" style="color:#d73a49">make</span><span class="token plain"> compile</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div><p>and after you execute the building process, you can run the node using this command:</p><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">$ </span><span class="token function" style="color:#d73a49">make</span><span class="token plain"> run</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div><h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="using-docker">Using Docker<a class="hash-link" href="#using-docker" title="Direct link to heading">‚Äã</a></h3><p>If you want to keep your environment clean and run Juno in a Docker container, use the following command:</p><div class="codeBlockContainer_I0IT language-bash theme-code-block"><div class="codeBlockContent_wNvx bash"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_jd64 thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_mRuA"><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">docker run -p </span><span class="token number" style="color:#36acaa">8080</span><span class="token plain">:8080 -v juno_data:/home/app/.config/juno/data -v /path/to/your/config/file/juno.yaml:/home/app/.config/juno/juno.yaml juno</span><br></span></code></pre><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" class="copyButton_wuS7 clean-btn">Copy</button></div></div><p>For more details, see the docker documentation page.</p>]]></content>
